    "recap_headline": "Davidson College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DAVIDSON \u2014 Davidson and Fordham will meet in a Sunday rubber game after the visiting Rams evened the Atlantic 10 weekend series with a 6-4 win at Wilson Field Saturday afternoon.\nThe loss ended the Wildcats' win streak at five games and dropped them to 9-8 overall and 1-1 in league play. Fordham (7-10) is also 1-1 in the A-10.\nRams starting pitcher Chase Hamawalt struck out 13 and held the Wildcats to one hit \u2014 an\nAnthony Torreso\nfourth-inning single \u2014 for six innings before the Wildcats broke through. The Rams led 6-0 when\nTheo Loughlin\ndrove in two on a bases-loaded single in the seventh.\nDavidson threatened in the ninth, getting two runners aboard with no outs and pushing both across. But the Rams closed the door with the tying run at the plate.\nTorreso and Loughlin had two hits apiece, and Loughlin had three RBIs.\nStarter\nCooper Cavanaugh\nthrew 3.1 innings, allowed four hits and two earned runs and struck out three.\nUp Next\nSunday's first pitch is set for 1 p.m."
